        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="7">
            <title>service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property, personal injury or death park the vehicle on a flat level surface, set the
                        parking brake, chock the brakes, and turn the engine off.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always use floor stands to support the vehicle before working under it. Using only a jack
                        could allow the vehicle to fall resulting in property damage, personal injury, or death.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The following Steps are for one side of the IROS system. It will be repeated on the opposite
                        side.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure and record the rear axle alignment on
                    <emph type="bold">both sides</emph>
                    of the bus by measuring the horizontal distance between the wheel rim and the inner edge of the
                    wheel well as shown in Figure 1. Place a mark on the rim and the wheel well to indicate the two
                    points used to make the measurement. Use a level to insure the measurement points remain in the same
                    plane during both before and after measurements.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The recorded dimensions will be used to determine if shimming is required after the new
                            components are installed.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049091" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049097a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Measure Horizontal Dimension Between Arrows</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise the chassis rear end and support from the frame rails with floor stands.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the vehicle air system.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the IROS ride height control rod and ride height valve assembly (Figure 2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049092" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049091.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Remove Ride Height Control Rod and Valve Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Ride Height Valve</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Ride Height Control Rod</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect air lines from the IROS air springs.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting bolts and the air spring (Figure 3).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049093" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049092.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Remove Mounting Bolts and Air Spring</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting bolts and shock absorber.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a jack under the axle carrier to raise the axle assembly then place floor stands
                    under the axle assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the IROS spring U-bolts and lower U-bolt plate (Figure 4).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049094" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049093.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Remove IROS Spring U-Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. U-Bolts</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Lower U-Bolt Plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove IROS spring bushing mounting bolts and remove the IROS spring (Figure 5).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049095" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049094.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Remove Spring Bushing Bolts, Shown at Arrows</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The IROS springs in the Kit are not interchangeable. When installing the new spring, ensure
                        the correct part number is used for the side being serviced.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new IROS spring to the spring hanger, install new bushing bar pin bolts and
                    nuts (Figure 6). Tighten to 370 to 460 Lbf-ft (502 to 624 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049096" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049095.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Install new IROS Spring to Spring Hanger</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Spring Hanger</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Bushing Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a jack to raise the new IROS spring into position, use a new axle seat (Figure 7,
                    Item 6) from the kit, between the IROS spring and the axle, reuse the top u-bolt plate (Figure 7,
                    Item 3) and install a new lower u-bolt plate (Figure 7, Item 5). Install new u-bolts, washers and
                    nuts (Figure 7, Item 4) from the kit and at this time tighten only enough to hold the axle in
                    position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049097" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049096a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. IROS Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Air Spring</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Shock Absorber</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Top U-Bolt Plate</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. U-Bolt, Washer, and Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. Lower U-Bolt Plate</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. Axle Seat</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new shock absorber (Figure 7, Item 2) from the kit. Tighten to 135 to 165
                    Lbf-ft (183 to 224 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new air spring (Figure 7, Item 1) from the kit. Tighten mounting nuts to 40 to
                    60 Lbf-ft (54 to 81 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat Steps 4 - 14 for the opposite side then continue to Step 16.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new ride height valve and rod from the kit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the air lines to the ride height valve.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the air lines to the ride height valve and air springs.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove floor stands and jack.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start the engine to charge the air system and check for air leaks.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to TSI-04-03-01, Air Suspension Adjustment Specifications, to ensure the axle
                    travel is set to the correct specification. Adjust as needed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat the measurements made in Step 1, between the marked points, and compare them to
                    the original dimensions. Shims are included in the kit to adjust the alignment. NOTE: If shims are
                    required, place the shim between the spring hanger and the IROS bushing. If there is a large
                    difference side to side you must slide the axle at the spring mounting.
                </para>
                <para>It is more important that the difference in the two measurements is maintained than the absolute
                    value of the number is maintained.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After the alignment is properly set, tighten the spring U-bolts to 400 to 450 Lbf-ft
                    (542 to 610 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
